# FRONS Ecosystem — Claude Code Instructions

You are building the FRONS ecosystem: an on-chain research library, an evidence-based AI chat engine, an encrypted personal vault, NFC identity cards, and a master admin console. The entire system runs on Solana blockchain for payments and verification, Supabase for metadata, Walrus for decentralized storage, and Next.js for all frontends.

## Core Products

1. **Fronsciers** (fronsciers.id) — On-chain peer-reviewed research library. Scientists publish papers, earn citations, get paid when AI uses their work. Every AI citation triggers a $0.01 micro-payment split 40% platform / 20% author / 20% sharing pool / 20% reserve.

2. **Frons.id** (frons.id) — Evidence-based AI chat engine with zero hallucinations. Uses a 4-tier evidence cascade: Fronsciers → PubMed → Scopus → honest admission. Charges credits per question (3–10 credits, $0.03–$0.10). Never fabricates sources.

3. **My Vault** — Encrypted personal data vault. Google Drive-like interface for medical records, research datasets, manuscripts. Client-side AES-256-GCM encryption — the platform never sees plaintext data. Stored on Walrus with SHA-256 proof on Solana.

4. **Fronsciers NFC Card** (card.fronsciers.id) — Physical NTAG 424 DNA card. Tap on any phone → public research portfolio. Rolling CMAC authentication prevents cloning.

5. **Admin Console** — Isolated high-security admin portal. Manages Solana protocol parameters, ecosystem analytics, and direct evidence seeding into the AI database.

## Hard Requirements

- Users never see gas fees, wallet addresses, or seed phrases. Privy handles wallet creation silently. SOL gas is escrowed from subscription payments.
- The platform cannot read user vault data. All encryption happens in the browser. Even metadata (file names, tags) is encrypted.
- AI and researchers access only synthetic datasets generated from originals. Privacy preserved via k-anonymity + differential privacy.
- On-chain micro-payments for every AI access to research content.
- Better to admit "insufficient evidence" than to hallucinate. No source = no claim.
- All payments support three rails: Stripe (global), Xendit/QRIS (Indonesia), USDC on Solana (crypto).
- Target market is Indonesian researchers and patients. IDR pricing via Xendit/QRIS. Interface supports Bahasa Indonesia.

## Why Solana

Sub-cent fees (~$0.001 per tx), sub-second settlement, mature JS SDK (@solana/web3.js), and expressive smart contracts via Anchor/Rust. A full citation lifecycle costs about $0.001. Ethereum would cost $5+ per transaction — unacceptable for $0.01 micro-payments.

## Why Supabase

Built-in full-text search with weighted ranking, row-level security, real-time subscriptions, auth integration, generous free tier. PostgreSQL under the hood — no vendor lock-in.

## Why Walrus

Programmable decentralized storage with 4.5x replication (not 100x like IPFS). Cost-effective for encrypted blobs. Integrates with Solana for integrity proofs.

---

## Architecture Design Reviews

ADR-1: Evidence cascade searches Fronsciers first because that earns authors money. External sources (PubMed, Scopus) are fallbacks. Honest admission ("insufficient evidence") is the final tier. This ordering is non-negotiable — it is the core monetization mechanism.

ADR-2: Client-side AES-256-GCM encryption for all vault data. Key derivation uses PBKDF2 with wallet signature as entropy, 100,000 iterations, SHA-512. Sub-keys derived via HKDF: one for file encryption (FEK), one for metadata encryption (MEK). The server never touches plaintext or keys. Recovery via 12-word phrase generated at vault setup.

ADR-3: Synthetic data pipeline transforms original datasets through three stages: STRIP (remove identifiers, generalize quasi-identifiers to 5-year age bands), PERTURB (Laplace noise with ε=1.0, preserve distributions), COMPRESS (type optimization + Parquet/Snappy for 75% size reduction). Privacy guarantee: k=5 anonymity + ε-differential privacy.

ADR-4: Credit system uses atomic PostgreSQL functions to prevent race conditions and negative balances. Every credit spend records revenue splits in the same transaction. 1 credit = $0.01 USD.

ADR-5: NFC cards use NTAG 424 DNA chips with rolling CMAC authentication. Each tap generates a unique SUN (Secure Unique NFC) message that the server validates against the card's stored key. Counter increments prevent replay attacks. The CMAC verification happens server-side — the tap URL contains the encrypted payload.

ADR-6: Privy handles all wallet creation silently. Users authenticate via email, Google, or existing Solana wallet. Privy creates an embedded wallet invisibly. Gas fees are pre-escrowed from subscription payments and spent on behalf of the user via server-side signing.

ADR-7: Subscriptions cover infrastructure costs (vault storage, gas escrow, file limits). Credits cover variable AI compute costs. This hybrid model ensures predictable revenue while fairly pricing usage. Free tier gets 20 credits and 100MB — enough to try the product.

ADR-8: Anti-crawl protection blocks known AI training bots (GPTBot, ClaudeBot, CCBot, etc.) via user-agent matching. API rate limiting enforces per-hour and per-day caps. Unauthorized access to full-text content requires payment via x402 HTTP middleware.

ADR-9: The MCP server exposes Fronsciers content to AI assistants via the Model Context Protocol. Search and abstracts are free (discovery). Full-text access triggers citation payment. This makes Fronsciers content available across all AI platforms while ensuring authors get paid.

ADR-10: Each frontend runs as an independent Next.js application. Shared Privy authentication ensures users have one identity across all products. Supabase provides the shared data layer. Solana provides the shared payment layer.

---

## System Architecture

```
                         Users (Researchers, Patients, Doctors)
                                       │
          ┌────────────────┬───────────┼───────────┬────────────────┐
          │                │           │           │                │
    ┌─────▼──────┐  ┌─────▼──────┐ ┌──▼───┐ ┌────▼─────┐  ┌──────▼──────┐
    │ Frons.id   │  │ Fronsciers │ │ Vault│ │ NFC Card │  │ Admin       │
    │ (AI Chat)  │  │ (Library)  │ │      │ │ (Profile)│  │ (Console)   │
    │ Port 3002  │  │ Port 3000  │ │ 3002 │ │ Port 3003│  │ Port 3004   │
    └─────┬──────┘  └─────┬──────┘ └──┬───┘ └────┬─────┘  └──────┬──────┘
          │                │           │           │                │
          └────────────────┴───────────┼───────────┴────────────────┘
                                       │
                    ┌──────────────────┼──────────────────┐
                    │                  │                  │
              ┌─────▼──────┐   ┌──────▼──────┐   ┌──────▼──────┐
              │ MCP Server │   │ Supabase    │   │ Solana      │
              │ (FastMCP)  │   │ (Database)  │   │ (Payments)  │
              │ Python     │   │ PostgreSQL  │   │ Anchor/Rust │
              └─────┬──────┘   └──────┬──────┘   └──────┬──────┘
                    │                  │                  │
              ┌─────▼──────┐   ┌──────▼──────┐   ┌──────▼──────┐
              │ External   │   │ Walrus      │   │ Jupiter     │
              │ APIs       │   │ (Files)     │   │ (SOL swap)  │
              │ PubMed     │   │ Decentralized│  │ Auto gas    │
              │ Scopus     │   │ Encrypted   │   │ purchase    │
              │ CrossRef   │   │ Storage     │   │             │
              └────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘
```

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Blockchain | Solana (latest) | Payments, NFTs, citations, integrity proofs |
| Smart Contract | Rust + Anchor 0.31.0 | On-chain logic for submissions, citations, escrow |
| Database | Supabase (PostgreSQL) | Full-text search, metadata, users, analytics, RLS |
| Frontend | Next.js 15 + React 19 + Tailwind v4 | All web applications |
| AI Gateway | Python 3.11+ + FastMCP | MCP server for Claude/AI access to Fronsciers |
| API Paywall | x402 HTTP middleware | Pay-per-citation for AI access |
| Auth | Privy (latest) | Embedded wallets, social login, unified identity |
| Encrypted Storage | Walrus (mainnet) | Decentralized file storage for vault and manuscripts |
| NFC | NTAG 424 DNA | Physical card authentication with rolling CMAC |
| Payments | Stripe + Xendit + USDC | Global + Indonesia + crypto payment rails |
| Frontend Hosting | Vercel | CDN + serverless for all Next.js apps |
| Server Hosting | Railway | MCP server + Solana indexer |

