## Smart Contract (Solana/Anchor)

Build 1 Anchor program with modular instruction handlers.

### Program: fronsciers

```
programs/fronsciers/src/
├── lib.rs
├── state.rs
├── constants.rs
├── error.rs
└── instructions/
    ├── mod.rs
    ├── initialize_protocol.rs
    ├── register_user.rs
    ├── submit_manuscript.rs       -- $50 USDC → split 40/30/10/20
    ├── review_manuscript.rs       -- 3-reviewer consensus
    ├── publish_manuscript.rs      -- Mint DOCI NFT
    ├── record_citation.rs         -- $0.01 per AI citation (THE CORE)
    ├── distribute_pool.rs         -- Monthly leaderboard distribution
    ├── claim_earnings.rs          -- Author withdraws accumulated USDC
    ├── update_impact_score.rs     -- Oracle updates metrics
    └── manage_protocol.rs         -- Admin controls
```

### Constants (CRITICAL: USDC has 6 decimals on Solana)
```rust
pub const SUBMISSION_FEE: u64 = 50_000_000;       // $50 USDC
pub const CITATION_FEE: u64 = 10_000;             // $0.01 USDC
pub const FRONS_ID_FEE: u64 = 20_000_000;         // $20 USDC
pub const REJECTION_KEEP: u64 = 5_000_000;         // $5 kept on rejection

pub const PLATFORM_FEE_BPS: u16 = 4000;           // 40%
pub const SHARING_POOL_BPS: u16 = 3000;            // 30%
pub const AUTHOR_DIRECT_BPS: u16 = 1000;           // 10%
pub const PROTOCOL_RESERVE_BPS: u16 = 2000;        // 20%

pub const CHAT_PLATFORM_BPS: u16 = 4000;           // 40%
pub const CHAT_AUTHOR_BPS: u16 = 2000;             // 20% (when Fronsciers cited)
pub const CHAT_POOL_BPS: u16 = 2000;               // 20%
pub const CHAT_RESERVE_BPS: u16 = 2000;             // 20%
```

### State Accounts
```rust
#[account]
pub struct ProtocolState {
    pub authority: Pubkey,
    pub treasury: Pubkey,
    pub sharing_pool: Pubkey,
    pub reserve: Pubkey,
    pub total_submissions: u64,
    pub total_citations: u64,
    pub total_revenue_usdc: u64,
    pub current_epoch: u64,
    pub platform_fee_bps: u16,
    pub pool_fee_bps: u16,
    pub author_fee_bps: u16,
    pub reserve_fee_bps: u16,
    pub citation_fee: u64,
    pub submission_fee: u64,
    pub paused: bool,
    pub bump: u8,
}

#[account]
pub struct AuthorVault {
    pub author: Pubkey,
    pub total_earned: u64,
    pub claimable: u64,
    pub total_citations: u64,
    pub impact_score: u64,
    pub last_claim_epoch: u64,
    pub bump: u8,
}

#[derive(AnchorSerialize, AnchorDeserialize, Clone, PartialEq)]
pub enum ManuscriptStatus {
    Pending,
    InReview,
    Accepted,
    Rejected,
    Published,
}
```

### Instructions

1. `initialize_protocol(platform_fee_bps, pool_fee_bps, author_fee_bps, reserve_fee_bps)` — Creates ProtocolState PDA. Sets treasury, sharing pool, and reserve token accounts. Only callable once.

2. `register_user(name, email, institution)` — Creates researcher account with Privy-provided wallet. Initializes credit balance with signup bonus (20 credits). Creates gas escrow account.

3. `submit_manuscript(title, abstract, content, authors, keywords, field)` — Transfers $50 USDC submission fee. Splits: 40% platform, 30% sharing pool, 10% author deposit, 20% reserve. Creates on-chain manuscript account with status=Pending. Stores Walrus blob ID for encrypted full text.

4. `review_manuscript(article_id, decision, feedback)` — Only callable by assigned reviewers. Records decision (accept/reject/revise). When 3 reviewers submit and ≥2 agree: auto-advance status. Reviewer earns 30 credit bonus.

5. `publish_manuscript(article_id)` — Only callable when status=Accepted. Mints DOCI NFT using Metaplex Token Metadata. Sets status=Published. Generates DOI-format identifier (10.fronsciers/YYYY.NNNN).

6. `record_citation(article_id, citing_agent, context)` — THE CORE INSTRUCTION. Charges $0.01 USDC. Splits: 40% platform, 20% author (direct to AuthorVault), 20% sharing pool, 20% reserve. Increments article citation count. Updates author impact score. Emits CitationEvent. This is called by the MCP server every time AI cites a Fronsciers paper.

7. `distribute_pool(period)` — Monthly cron. Distributes sharing pool based on leaderboard scores (PCS + SSS + TIS). Top researchers earn proportional payouts.

8. `claim_earnings()` — Author withdraws accumulated USDC from their AuthorVault to their wallet.

9. `update_impact_score(researcher_id, new_score)` — Oracle-only. Updates researcher impact metrics from off-chain computation.

10. `manage_protocol(new_fees, pause)` — Admin-only. Updates fee BPS, pauses/unpauses protocol.

